The native compiler (cpp/compile/) copies specific algorithms from the vendored
MuJoCo source tree (pin mjVERSION_HEADER 3010000 / MuJoCo 3.10.0) into
cpp/compile/lifted/ with provenance headers. Each lifted symbol or file is
recorded in snapshots/lifted_code.json together with the exact upstream text at
lift time (snapshots/lifted_upstream/) and is drift-gated against the vendored
tree by tools/lift_registry.py. The lifted code retains its Apache-2.0 license;
adaptations (namespacing, error-type retargeting, data-plumbing changes) are
noted per entry in the registry.

Currently lifted:
  - src/user/user_util.{h,cc}   the mjuu_* free-standing math/util pool
  - src/engine/engine_io.c      mj_makeModel, mj_setPtrModel,
                                safeAddToBufferSize, SKIP (mjModel allocation)
